svg.title: Clouds of the genera Cirrus, Cirrocumulus and Cirrostratus: Cirrus uncinus or fibratus, or both, progressively invading the sky; they generally thicken as a whole
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: Clouds of the genera Cirrus, Cirrocumulus and Cirrostratus: Cirrus in the form of hooks or of filaments, or both, progressively invading the sky; they generally become denser as a whole
